question2.S: Easy to navigate, some problems of displaying properly specifically on the grouping page.

question3.S: First check them to instantly eliminate ones that the person does not want to do, then rank the ones they want to do, then score them. letting them get rid of a few options at the start makes ranking them easier, then using the score method lets them show if there are any that they equally do/donâ€™t want to do. Using a combination of methods would be more efficient than just trying to order the methods from best to worst then picking the best one.

question5.S: instead of only using the rank method at the end page (for score, rank, group and check) you should also use the scoring method, as some people may find two of these methods equally good. also when working with a smaller number of things to rank it makes it seem like there is a big jump in how good each of the methods are as you go down the ranking. the score method would be able to show numerically how close each of the methods are in terms of how good they are.
